ref\":\"#introduction\",\"aria-label\":\"introduction permalink\"},`\\xbb`),`Introduction`),mdx(\"p\",null,`Terraform commands that generate Terraform configuration produce\nconfiguration files that conform to the style imposed by `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),`. Follow this style in your files to ensure consistency.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`The canonical format may change in minor ways between Terraform versions, so\nafter upgrading Terraform we recommend to proactively run `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),`\non your modules along with any other changes you are making to adopt the new\nversion.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`We do not consider new formatting rules in `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),` to be a breaking\nchange in new versions of Terraform, but we minimize changes for\nconfigurations that already follow the style examples shown in the\nTerraform documentation. New formatting rules programmed into the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),`\ncommand are usually expansions to include existing rules from the documentation.\nWe recommend following the documented style even for decisions that `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),`\ndoes not yet apply automatically.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`Formatting decisions are always subjective and so you might disagree with the\ndecisions that `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),` makes. This command is intentionally opinionated\nand has no customization options because its primary goal is to encourage\nconsistency of style between different Terraform codebases, even though the\nchosen style can never be everyone's favorite.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`We recommend that you follow the style conventions applied by `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),`\nwhen writing Terraform modules, but if you find the results particularly\nobjectionable then you may choose not to use this command, and possibly choose\nto use a third-party formatting tool instead. If you choose to use a\nthird-party tool then you should also run it on files that are generated\nautomatically by Terraform, to get consistency between your hand-written files\nand the generated files.`),mdx(\"h2\",{\"id\":\"usage\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"h2\",\"className\":\"__permalink-h\",\"href\":\"#usage\",\"aria-label\":\"usage permalink\"},`\\xbb`),`Usage`),mdx(\"p\",null,`Usage: `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt [options] [target...]`)),mdx(\"p\",null,`By default, the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),` command scans your current directory for configuration files. You can also provide a `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`target`),` argument to tell `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),` to scan:`),mdx(\"ul\",null,mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},`A directory `),mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},`A specific file`),mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},`Standard input by supplying a single dash (`,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"li\"},`-`),`).`)),mdx(\"p\",null,`The `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform fmt`),` command accepts the following arguments.`),mdx(\"table\",null,mdx(\"thead\",{parentName:\"table\"},mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"thead\"},mdx(\"th\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Flag`),mdx(\"th\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Description`),mdx(\"th\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Required`))),mdx(\"tbody\",{parentName:\"table\"},mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"tbody\"},mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-list=false`)),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Prevents the command from listing the files containing formatting inconsistencies.`),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Optional`)),mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"tbody\"},mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-diff`)),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Displays the diffs of formatting changes.`),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Optional`)),mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"tbody\"},mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-write=false`)),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Prevents the command from overwriting files. This behavior is implied by the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-check`),` flag or if the input is from `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`STDIN`),`.`),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Optional`)),mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"tbody\"},mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-check`)),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Checks if the input is formatted. The exit status is `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`0`),` if the command's input is properly formatted. Otherwise, the exit status is non-zero, and the command outputs a list of improperly formatted file names.`),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Optional`)),mdx(\"tr\",{parentName:\"tbody\"},mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"td\"},`-recursive`)),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Processes files in subdirectories in addition to the current directory. By default, the command only processes the specified, or current, directory.`),mdx(\"td\",{parentName:\"tr\",\"align\":\"left\"},`Optional`)))))};MDXContent.isMDXComponent=true;","scope":{"product":"terraform","version":"latest"}},"product":{"slug":"terraform","name":"Terraform","algoliaConfig":{"indexName":"product_TERRAFORM"},"alertBannerActive":true,"alertBanner":{"tag":"New","url":"https://www.hashicorp.com/blog/introducing-the-infrastructure-cloud","text":"Terraform Cloud is now HCP Terraform","linkText":"Read more â†’","expirationDate":"2024-04-29T00:00:00-08:00"},"basePaths":["cdktf","cli","cloud-docs","cloud-